This paper deals with coalition formation games, which are a subfield of game theory. Therefore, cs.GT (Game Theory and Mechanism Design) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses algorithms and computational complexity, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of preferences and hedonic games could also make it relevant to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper discusses stability concepts, which could make it relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
